<div class="context">
<h1 class="title">Pseudo Variables</h1>
<span class="subtitle"></span>
<!-- $$$strules-pseudo-variable-reference.html-description -->
<div class="descr"> <a name="details"></a>
<a name="build-mkspec"></a>
<h2 id="build-mkspec">BUILD_MKSPEC</h2>
<p>Specifies a subdirectory path based on toolkit mkspec shortname. In case of Qt-based project, this path will be suffixed by the Qt version used.</p>
<p>For example, for a 64-bit application built on Visual C++ 12.0, using Qt 5.6&#x2e;3 modules:</p>
<pre class="cpp">DESTDIR = &quot;builds/${BUILD_MKSPEC}&quot;   # application based on Qt: DESTDIR = &quot;builds/win-msvc2013-x64-QT5.6.3&quot;
CONFIG -= qt                         # application no more based on Qt: DESTDIR = &quot;builds/win-msvc2013-x64&quot;</pre>
<a name="delivery"></a>
<h2 id="delivery">DELIVERY</h2>
<p>Specifies the absolute path to installation package root directory, i.e&#x2e; <code>${<a href="strules-pseudo-variable-reference.html#package">PACKAGE</a>}/Delivery</code>.</p>
<a name="package"></a>
<h2 id="package">PACKAGE</h2>
<p>Specifies the absolute path to package containing current project.</p>
<p>See also <a href="strules-predefined-rules.html#projects-package">Projects Package</a>.</p>
</div>
